A dark cave. Water drips somewhere. A passage leads north.
A brass lamp glints on the floor.
You take the brass lamp. It hums faintly.
You carry: one faintly humming lamp.
You squeeze through the passage into daylight.
A sunny forest clearing. A cave mouth yawns to the south.
There is nothing here to take.
You duck into the gloom.
A dark cave. Water drips somewhere. A passage leads north.
A dark cave. Water drips somewhere. A passage leads north.
